President Obama has proclaimed November 1 through November 7, 2015, as National Apprenticeship Week in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of apprenticeships in providing individuals with the skills and resources they need to succeed in the 21st century. It emphasizes the benefits of apprenticeships for both workers and employers, including higher wages, increased productivity, reduced waste, and greater innovation. The proclamation also recognizes the efforts of businesses, educators, labor leaders, and elected officials in promoting and supporting apprenticeship programs. The Obama Administration has made significant investments in apprenticeships and job-driven training initiatives, and the proclamation calls on Congress and businesses to further support these programs. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to support apprenticeship programs and raise awareness of their contributions to the country.